Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Forward Deployed Engineer* with *Esper*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack engineering, distributed systems, and technical implementations, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across multiple engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *the complex interplay between Java 21 backend services, data migrations, and customer-facing technical delivery*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I engineered an MCP interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API design and the ability to lead end-to-end customer implementations from discovery to post-launch optimization. To ensure operational stability, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith, which surfaced architectural and data quality risks before they impacted production, ultimately reducing latency by 60%. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled critical data migrations and structured content onboarding across AWS S3, Google Cloud, and MinIO. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using React and Spring Boot (Java 21), supporting thousands of users while maintaining high security and compliance standards. Together, these roles have prepared me to *lead technical customer implementations and build reusable tools that accelerate the modernization of public policy workflows* and drive impact within an agile engineering team.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into *the data-driven decision-making and mission-oriented rigor this team values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the technical lifecycle of high-performance distributed systems, fine-tuning industry-standard models using CUDA and PyTorch on an HPC cluster. Beyond building the systems myself, I led technical workshops on GPU programming and AI Agents for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to explain complex system design decisions to both technical peers and non-technical stakeholders — directly mirroring *the technical communication and customer-advocacy responsibilities central to this role*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *Esper and its mission to transform government operations through technology*.


I have always been passionate about *simplifying regulatory complexities and empowering governments to deliver better outcomes* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *modernizing the regulatory and policy-making infrastructure of government*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

